##  Outcome
 -  LANDED `a8fa2e87`. The "off-by-one hashlet" hypothesis was WRONG —
    `0cb94e64e…` is a correct `%016llx`-padded value, not mangled. TWO
    independent bugs, both fixed: (1) server `keeper/WIRE.c` tripped on a
    degenerate *zero-length pack bookmark* (GET-025-era re-index) → shipped
    a 12-byte empty pack → `WIRECRPT`; now skips zero-len bookmarks. (2)
    `sniff/PUT.c` `PUTSetBranch` prepended a stray `?` → the `?#?<sha>`
    reset-row malformation; now records bare `?#<sha>`. +2 tests; 391/391.
    Live `~/.be/dogs` keeps the stray bookmark (server now tolerant).

